item.title: Michael Jackson Death ruled Homicide
item.dc:creator: @whothe0 the fu superior
item.description:
@whothe0 wrote:

[quote=“R.I.P RSC, post:24, topic:298480”][quote author=Thug-life link=topic=394878.msg2939623#msg2939623 date=1251770425]
Not trolling

Honestly, apart from seeing people talk about him dying. I had never heard of him till i Googled him just now, but that is irrelevant, i was trying to show you why Michael jackson’s death caused such a reaction within the media.

Michael jackson was, like him or not, one of the best musical entertainers this planet has seen. He was one of the few people still living who helped create the music industry we have now, regardless of genre. The hype around michael jackson wasn’t unfounded.

I understand its annoying hearing nothing but Michael jackson for weeks on end, but surely you can see why?
[/quote]

If he’d bring out a new album, I’d love to know it. But his personal life (or the absence of it) is something I really don’t care about. I really don’t care about the personal life of any celebrity. They either want to keep it a secret, or they are pieces of shit and keep on whining about their lives on tv. They should be known for what they did professionaly, not what they did in their private life. Being alive is to me a part of the private life, so I don’t care about it.[/quote]
So if Megan Fox spent her spare time fingering herself to pictures of you, and wanted to fuck you… you wouldn’t want to know?

item.description:

Yea. He was a music icon and the King of Pop. Everyone knew him, but half the people knew him for the wrong reason. Thats one of the things wrong with most people in this world now. In many peoples’ minds, it is “Guilty until proven innocent”, while it should rightfully be the other way around. If no-one ever though about MJ’s problems/issues, then maybe people wouldn’t be as annoyed as they are now with the news stretching this out for so long.
